WEBVTT

1
00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:50.640
-Is it a girl?
- Yes.

2
00:00:50.720 --> 00:00:52.400
Show me its arm.

3
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:55.240
- She bears the mark.
- No!

4
00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:01.120
The omen is true.
I must tell my mother.

5
00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:05.520
- Help me!
- I can't.

6
00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:08.240
- They're going to kill her.

7
00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:20.160
Oh. thank you. Ethna. Thank you.

8
00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:30.800
Stand aside for Queen Bavmorda!

9
00:01:54.160 --> 00:01:56.560
You cannot
stop the prophecy!

10
00:01:56.640 --> 00:01:59.440
This child will have no power over me.
Start the ritual.

11
00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:04.160
- No. No!
- Where's the baby?

12
00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:06.560
The midwife.
Find that baby. Sorsha.

13
00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:09.880
Use the dogs.
Bring her back to me alive!

14
00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:11.960
Your reign of terror
is at an end!

15
00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:14.040
She will come back.
and she will finish you!

16
00:02:14.120 --> 00:02:17.560
- Silence. wench.
- My baby will finish you!
- Kill her.

17
00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:38.240
Dada! Dada!

18
00:05:41.480 --> 00:05:44.680
-Dada! Dada!
- Whoa! Whoa!

19
00:05:45.840 --> 00:05:48.960
Dada! Dada!
We found something in the river.

20
00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:50.880
I can't run off and play
with you now. Ranon.

21
00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:53.160
- I've got work to do.
- You gotta come. Hurry!

22
00:05:57.960 --> 00:06:00.360
Come on.

23
00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:05.520
Don't go near it.
We don't know where it's been.

24
00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:08.400
But. Dada. it's a baby.

25
00:06:08.480 --> 00:06:13.080
- It's not like us.
- No. It's not a Nelwyn.

26
00:06:13.160 --> 00:06:16.600
- It looks like a Daikini baby.
- What's a Daikini?

27
00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:18.880
Daikinis are big.

28
00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:21.920
- Giants who live far away.

29
00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.200
Oh. she's so cute.

30
00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:28.160
- Can't we keep it. Dada?
- No!

31
00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:33.240
We'll push it downstream and forget
we ever saw it. Come on.

32
00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:35.160
- Come on.
- Ufgood! Willow Ufgood!

33
00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:39.200
Shhh! It's the prefect.
That's all I need.

34
00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:42.600
Keep it quiet.
Don't touch it.

35
00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:47.760
Mr. Burglekutt. my husband
hasn't stolen anything!

36
00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:49.720
Baaa!

37
00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:56.360
Ufgood. you still haven't
paid your debts to me.

38
00:06:56.440 --> 00:06:58.360
Where did you
get these seeds?

39
00:06:58.440 --> 00:07:01.080
Well. maybe I used magic.

40
00:07:01.160 --> 00:07:04.920
You're no sorcerer. Ufgood.
You're a clown.

41
00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:08.440
I sell the planting seeds around here.
Now tell me where you got them.

42
00:07:08.480 --> 00:07:11.840
My family's been gathering them
in the forest since last fall.

43
00:07:11.920 --> 00:07:14.800
- There's no law against that.

44
00:07:14.880 --> 00:07:19.840
Willow. you didn't leave
them alone by the river?

45
00:07:19.880 --> 00:07:22.160
Magic?
You'll need magic...

46
00:07:22.240 --> 00:07:24.480
if you expect to get your planting
done before the rains start.

47
00:07:26.440 --> 00:07:31.720
I will have this land. And you're
gonna end up working in the mines.

48
00:07:33.840 --> 00:07:37.440
- Baaa-

49
00:07:40.440 --> 00:07:43.320
Oh. you're lovely.

50
00:07:43.360 --> 00:07:45.280
- Yes. you are.

51
00:07:45.360 --> 00:07:49.640
- Kiaya!
- Oh. Willow!

52
00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:54.400
- Good girl. Good girl.
- Under no condition whatsoever...

53
00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:57.120
is anyone in this family
to fall in love with that baby.

54
00:07:57.160 --> 00:08:01.720
Yes. you are. Come on. Mims.
Come on. Come on.

55
00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:03.760
There we are. Come on.

56
00:08:03.840 --> 00:08:06.360
Hey. I will not be ignored!

57
00:08:06.440 --> 00:08:10.000
Mims? Ranon?

58
00:08:20.520 --> 00:08:22.560
- You're gonna be all clean.

59
00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:32.120
Willow. do you think we should
take her to the village council?

60
00:08:32.200 --> 00:08:34.680
No. No.
They'll think it's a bad omen.

61
00:08:34.760 --> 00:08:37.440
There'll be a flood or a drought.
and everyone will blame me for it.

62
00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:40.320
"Willow Ufgood brought around
that Daikini. didn't he?

63
00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:43.280
That's right. He's that
lousy farmer too. Let's get him!

64
00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:47.240
- Willow. calm down.
- Calm down?

65
00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:49.320
Kiaya. tomorrow's my big day.

66
00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:53.000
Love. the High Aldwin hasn't
picked a new apprentice in years.

67
00:08:53.040 --> 00:08:56.160
Tomorrow's gonna be different.
I just know he's gonna pick me.

68
00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:02.360
- Here. Hold her.
- Hey. no. I don't want her. Kiaya.

69
00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:05.120
- Hold her while I get some milk.
- Oh. no. no. Oh.

70
00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:15.720
- Dada. she likes you.

71
00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:23.560
- Bye.

72
00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:26.560
- Bye.

73
00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:30.400
- Come on. kids. Let's go.

74
00:09:36.200 --> 00:09:39.600
I will now magic ally join the rings!

75
00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:03.200
- Whoa-ah!

76
00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:10.080
Thank you. son.

77
00:10:10.120 --> 00:10:14.960
If you're easily shocked.
please turn away.

78
00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:31.680
Give me a ripe one. Good.

79
00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:41.960
- And now. for my final amazing feat.

80
00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:46.680
- I will make this entire pig disappear!

81
00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:59.360
- Mims. see?
- Please. watch very closely.

82
00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:04.800
- Wuppitybairn. deru. deru!

83
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.280
- Well-
- What happened to your pig?

84
00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:14.800
No!
Hey. come here. you!

85
00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:22.320
I had seen enough.

86
00:11:36.840 --> 00:11:40.000
Attention!
The High Aldwin...

87
00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:42.840
-will now make his choice
for his new apprentice!
- You'll be all right.

88
00:11:42.880 --> 00:11:46.240
Bring forth the hopefuls.

89
00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.600
- Good luck.
- Good luck. Dada.

90
00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:52.280
Willow Ufgood. a hopeful?
How did he get picked?

91
00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:54.760
Is this a joke?

92
00:11:54.840 --> 00:11:59.120
- Willow?

93
00:12:01.440 --> 00:12:06.640
Magic is the bloodstream
of the universe!

94
00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:11.080
Forget all you know...
or think you know.

95
00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:15.000
All that your require
is your intuition.

96
00:12:15.080 --> 00:12:19.040
Now. the power
to control the world...

97
00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:23.440
is in which finger?

98
00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:08.040
- No apprentice this year!

99
00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:30.800
- Where's Mims?
- I don't know. She was right here!

100
00:13:30.880 --> 00:13:33.720
Take Ranon in there. quick!

101
00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:44.080
- Mims!

102
00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:47.440
- Mims!

103
00:13:55.360 --> 00:14:00.000
- Mims!
- Dada-

104
00:14:01.240 --> 00:14:04.200
- I'm scared. Dada!

105
00:14:14.040 --> 00:14:16.520
Come on!

106
00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:36.280
- Vohnkar!

107
00:14:45.440 --> 00:14:48.240
- Check to make sure.
- It's dead!

108
00:14:50.440 --> 00:14:52.160
Dada! Dada!

109
00:14:55.400 --> 00:14:57.560
It was looking
for somebody's baby!

110
00:15:00.480 --> 00:15:04.120
- Mommy.
- Kiaya!

111
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:14.400
Kiaya!
Kiaya!

112
00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:17.360
- I'm here.

113
00:15:21.240 --> 00:15:24.760
- Oh. Kiaya.

114
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:26.920
We can't keep
the baby. Kiaya.

115
00:15:26.960 --> 00:15:29.720
We have to take her
to the village council.

116
00:15:42.680 --> 00:15:47.360
Silence! One beast we can kill.
but there may be more.

117
00:15:47.440 --> 00:15:49.760
And you can be assured
that they won't give up...

118
00:15:49.840 --> 00:15:51.720
until they find what
they're looking for!

119
00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:54.880
-It's a sign!
- Who's to blame for this?

120
00:15:54.960 --> 00:15:57.400
We must find the culprit
and throw him in the pit!

121
00:15:57.440 --> 00:16:02.360
- In the pit! In the pit!

122
00:16:02.400 --> 00:16:04.440
In the pit! In the pit!

123
00:16:04.560 --> 00:16:07.720
-In the pit! In the pit!
- Willow.

124
00:16:07.800 --> 00:16:11.920
- Willow Ufgood.

125
00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.400
Come forward.

126
00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:24.920
My children found this baby
alone by the river. High Aldwin.

127
00:16:30.320 --> 00:16:32.360
- A Daikini child.

128
00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:35.520
That's what the beasts want.
Let's give it back to them!

129
00:16:35.640 --> 00:16:36.680
Yeah!

130
00:16:36.760 --> 00:16:39.880
- They'll kill her! You can't!
- It isn't one of us.

131
00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:42.520
This child is special!

132
00:16:42.600 --> 00:16:46.680
This child must be taken beyond
the boundaries of our village.

133
00:16:46.760 --> 00:16:49.720
All the way across
the great river...

134
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.800
to the Daikini crossroads.

135
00:16:51.880 --> 00:16:56.400
- Well. who'll do that?
- It seems only fair...

136
00:16:56.440 --> 00:16:59.640
that the man to take
this baby to the crossroads...

137
00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:02.560
be the very man who
plucked it out of the river.

138
00:17:04.120 --> 00:17:06.640
- I nominate Willow Ufgood.

139
00:17:06.680 --> 00:17:09.080
No!

140
00:17:09.200 --> 00:17:12.600
I will consult the bones!

141
00:17:19.680 --> 00:17:24.920
- The bones tell me... nothing.

142
00:17:26.560 --> 00:17:30.320
Do you have any love
for this child?

143
00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:42.640
Yes. Yes. I do.

144
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:47.000
- The bones have spoken!

145
00:17:47.040 --> 00:17:50.840
Willow Ufgood. the safety
of this village depends upon you.

146
00:17:50.920 --> 00:17:54.800
- Praise the bones!
- Praise the bones!

147
00:17:54.880 --> 00:17:57.320
But you will need help.

148
00:17:57.400 --> 00:18:02.480
Who has the courage to protect
our brave fellow on his journey?

149
00:18:04.440 --> 00:18:08.440
- I'll go with him.
- Ah. Meegosh.

150
00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:11.640
- Excellent choice.
- I'll go!

151
00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:14.080
Vohnkar! Vohnkar!

152
00:18:14.160 --> 00:18:16.760
No! Not vohnkar!
He's the best warrior in the village!

153
00:18:16.800 --> 00:18:19.880
We need him here!
Vohnkar. step back!

154
00:18:27.560 --> 00:18:30.040
All this expedition needs
is a leader.

155
00:18:30.120 --> 00:18:33.360
And according to the bones...

156
00:18:33.400 --> 00:18:36.680
- Bh-
-That leader is...

157
00:18:36.760 --> 00:18:38.080
...you. Burglekutt!

158
00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:39.040
you. Burglekutt!

159
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.480
vohnkar!

160
00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:46.440
- What's your problem. son?
- How do you mean?

161
00:18:46.520 --> 00:18:51.640
When I held up my fingers
what was your first impulse?

162
00:18:51.720 --> 00:18:55.480
- Well. it was stupid.
-Just tell me.

163
00:18:55.520 --> 00:18:59.800
- To pick my own finger.
- Aha! That was the correct answer.

164
00:18:59.880 --> 00:19:04.400
You lack faith in yourself.
More than anyone in the village.

165
00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:06.960
you have the potential
to be a great sorcerer.

166
00:19:07.040 --> 00:19:11.680
Now. when you're out there.
listen to your own heart.

167
00:19:13.560 --> 00:19:18.360
- These will protect you. They're magic!
- Acorns?

168
00:19:18.440 --> 00:19:22.320
Anything you throw them at
turns to stone.

169
00:19:25.280 --> 00:19:28.360
You have much to learn.
young Ufgood.

170
00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:45.040
- Are you scared. Dada?
- No!

171
00:19:45.120 --> 00:19:49.160
Even with fairies in the woods that'll
put you to sleep for a hundred years?

172
00:19:51.120 --> 00:19:53.120
- Doesn't bother me.
- Brownies?

173
00:19:53.240 --> 00:19:56.040
- Dragons?
- Trolls?

174
00:19:56.120 --> 00:19:59.400
Trolls that'll skin you alive
and take your face off?

175
00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:02.960
Ranon!
You know I hate trolls.

176
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.000
I can be your guard
and carry your spear.

177
00:20:06.040 --> 00:20:07.600
Me too. Me too. Dada.

178
00:20:09.120 --> 00:20:14.240
What a lucky father I am. I wish
I could take you bobbins with me.

179
00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:19.640
Good-bye. Dada.

180
00:20:21.600 --> 00:20:25.440
Go play!
Go on.

181
00:20:29.240 --> 00:20:32.640
We've never been apart.

182
00:20:33.640 --> 00:20:36.840
I miss you already.

183
00:20:38.080 --> 00:20:41.400
Don't worry. Kiaya.
I'll be fine.

184
00:20:41.480 --> 00:20:43.320
I'll be back
before you know it.

185
00:20:45.440 --> 00:20:48.120
Well. remember
to keep her warm.

186
00:20:50.040 --> 00:20:52.680
And... here.

187
00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:57.400
This will bring you luck.

188
00:21:10.040 --> 00:21:12.280
Good brave people!

189
00:21:14.040 --> 00:21:16.680
The outer world is
no place for a Nelwyn.

190
00:21:16.760 --> 00:21:21.280
Give the baby to the first
Daikini you see. then hurry home.

191
00:21:24.640 --> 00:21:28.080
Tuatha...
lokwathrak... tuatha!

192
00:21:28.160 --> 00:21:31.560
Going the direction the bird is flying!

193
00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:35.400
- Ooh.

194
00:21:35.480 --> 00:21:38.200
It's going back to the village!

195
00:21:39.960 --> 00:21:41.840
Ignore the bird.
Follow the river.

196
00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:44.080
Move out!

197
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:10.360
- Hold on. Meegosh.
- What's wrong?

198
00:22:10.440 --> 00:22:14.320
- We have to stop.
- Stop? Why?

199
00:22:14.360 --> 00:22:16.760
- The baby's sick.

200
00:22:20.560 --> 00:22:24.960
She's not sick!
Let me see.

201
00:22:25.040 --> 00:22:28.120
Uhaghh!
Take her! Take her!

202
00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:33.560
She'll be fine
once she gets some rest.

203
00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:37.400
Clean me up.

204
00:22:40.920 --> 00:22:44.000
I didn't ask you
to bring me a dead nursemaid.

205
00:22:44.080 --> 00:22:47.840
-Sorsha. you're useless!
-I'm backtracking the nursemaid's trail.

206
00:22:47.880 --> 00:22:49.960
I'll find where
she hid the baby.

207
00:22:51.880 --> 00:22:54.040
Ah. General Kael. at last.

208
00:22:54.120 --> 00:22:58.640
My queen. I have destroyed
the castle at Galladoorn.

209
00:22:58.720 --> 00:23:02.240
Well done. But now I have
another task for you.

210
00:23:02.320 --> 00:23:07.600
Help my daughter to find
that tiny. helpless baby...

211
00:23:07.680 --> 00:23:09.560
that continues
somehow to elude her.

212
00:23:11.400 --> 00:23:13.280
The baby of the prophecy?

213
00:23:13.360 --> 00:23:16.640
- The one that would destroy you?
- I need that baby alive.

214
00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:19.040
I must perform
the ritual that will...

215
00:23:19.120 --> 00:23:22.360
exile the child's spirit
into oblivion.

216
00:23:22.440 --> 00:23:25.080
- Find her!
- I don't need his help. Mother.

217
00:23:25.120 --> 00:23:27.120
You'll do as I say. child.

218
00:23:33.280 --> 00:23:35.360
I read the signs.

219
00:23:35.440 --> 00:23:38.480
One day. I fear. your daughter
will betray you.

220
00:23:38.560 --> 00:23:42.520
I trust her loyalty
more than I trust yours.

221
00:23:57.640 --> 00:24:00.080
- Move!

222
00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:02.040
It's an ambush.
Come on. Move!

223
00:24:06.160 --> 00:24:09.680
- Come on!

224
00:24:18.920 --> 00:24:21.720
The Nelwyns have got the baby.
We've searched the village.

225
00:24:21.800 --> 00:24:24.640
But a group of them
Is on the road somewhere.

226
00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:26.480
They couldn' t have gone far!

227
00:24:26.480 --> 00:24:29.400
Widen the search
and report to Sorsha!

228
00:24:36.480 --> 00:24:39.080
Come. We'll keep to the woods.

229
00:25:16.240 --> 00:25:20.280
That's it!
It's the crossroads!

230
00:25:36.040 --> 00:25:38.880
Keep this fire high.
We don't know what's out there.

231
00:25:44.160 --> 00:25:46.560
- What was that?

232
00:25:47.840 --> 00:25:50.520
Get the spears!

233
00:26:06.280 --> 00:26:08.160
- Uhh. Uhh.

234
00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:11.920
Give me some water. peck.
or you die.

235
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:14.280
Do you understand?

236
00:26:14.400 --> 00:26:16.160
- Water.
- Yeah.

237
00:26:18.240 --> 00:26:20.160
Hurry up!

238
00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:26.800
Get me some water.
you measly little pecks.

239
00:26:26.880 --> 00:26:30.160
It's a Daikini.
We're in luck.

240
00:26:30.240 --> 00:26:32.600
We can't give her to him!

241
00:26:32.640 --> 00:26:36.440
- Somebody put him there for a reason.
- We've got to get rid of her.

242
00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:39.000
- Those soldiers are after us.
- Shhh.

243
00:26:39.080 --> 00:26:41.840
He's looking right at us.

244
00:26:45.600 --> 00:26:47.520
We've got to give
that baby to somebody.

245
00:26:47.560 --> 00:26:50.320
I'm somebody.

246
00:26:50.400 --> 00:26:54.520
Let me out of here. I'll take care
of the baby.

247
00:26:56.320 --> 00:27:00.760
- I trust him completely.
- But he tried to strangle me.

248
00:27:00.800 --> 00:27:04.600
- I want to go home!
- No. Burglekutt!

249
00:27:04.680 --> 00:27:07.880
- We should wait!
- Are you challenging my authority?

250
00:27:07.960 --> 00:27:11.200
As far as this baby
is concerned... yes.

251
00:27:11.240 --> 00:27:14.160
Don't listen to him. Burglekutt.

252
00:27:14.200 --> 00:27:19.120
Fine. You stay here alone.
but we're going.

253
00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:21.320
That's a bad idea.
Very bad.

254
00:27:21.400 --> 00:27:24.680
- Dangerous out there.
- Get the gear. men.

255
00:27:24.760 --> 00:27:28.160
- vohnkar-
- It's not his decision!

256
00:27:28.240 --> 00:27:32.000
Burglekutt. you're troll dung.

257
00:27:32.080 --> 00:27:33.680
Don't let him
talk to you that way.

258
00:27:33.800 --> 00:27:35.760
Listen here. runt.

259
00:27:35.800 --> 00:27:39.640
While you're wasting time here.
your fields aren't getting planted.

260
00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:43.840
- Think about it!
- Burglekutt. I'm gonna-

261
00:27:43.920 --> 00:27:47.160
You're gonna what?

262
00:27:50.880 --> 00:27:53.360
Some day. Burglekutt.
Some day.

263
00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:55.360
Vohnkar. let's go!

264
00:27:58.880 --> 00:28:01.480
Meegosh. are you coming?

265
00:28:03.680 --> 00:28:07.120
- I'm staying.
- Come on. men.

266
00:28:07.200 --> 00:28:11.200
Burglekutt. Let me out of here.
I'll take care of the baby. I swear.

267
00:28:11.280 --> 00:28:13.840
just let me out of here.
Please!

268
00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:17.240
Vohnkar. let me borrow that spear...
just for a minute.

269
00:28:17.280 --> 00:28:19.480
Get-
Well. at least get me some water!

270
00:28:19.520 --> 00:28:24.280
Burglekutt. don't leave me alone
with these two!

271
00:28:24.360 --> 00:28:28.960
- What'll we do now. Willow?

272
00:28:29.040 --> 00:28:31.560
Well. that was really stupid. peck.

273
00:28:31.640 --> 00:28:36.240
- Don't call me a peck.
- Oh. I'm sorry... peck.

274
00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:39.920
- Peck. peck. peck. peck.
- You be careful!

275
00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:43.600
I'm a powerful sorcerer.
See this acorn?

276
00:28:45.000 --> 00:28:49.280
- I'll throw it. and turn you to stone.
- Whoo-

277
00:28:49.360 --> 00:28:51.240
I'm really scared.

278
00:28:51.280 --> 00:28:54.040
No. don't! Don't!

279
00:28:54.080 --> 00:28:56.800
There's a peck here
with an acorn pointed at me!

280
00:28:56.880 --> 00:28:59.440
Oh. I wouldn't
want to waste it.

281
00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:02.640
Ha!
Peck. peck. peck. peck.

282
00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:05.160
peck. peck. peck.
peck. peck!

283
00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:35.360
- What was that?

284
00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:42.160
Mornin'. boys.

285
00:29:42.240 --> 00:29:46.200
Rough night last night.
wasn't it?

286
00:29:46.240 --> 00:29:49.480
I don't think I introduced
myself yesterday.

287
00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:52.880
My name is Madmartigan.
and you are. uh-

288
00:29:52.960 --> 00:29:55.800
No. Meegosh.
Don't go near him.

289
00:29:55.840 --> 00:29:59.160
- He's dangerous.
- I am not.

290
00:29:59.200 --> 00:30:01.280
Good.

291
00:30:05.840 --> 00:30:08.040
Stop! Wait!

292
00:30:09.720 --> 00:30:12.360
- Whoa!

293
00:30:17.600 --> 00:30:21.920
- What's going on?
- Smells like a battle.

294
00:30:22.000 --> 00:30:24.400
I suppose you're a warrior.

295
00:30:24.480 --> 00:30:26.880
I am the greatest swordsman
that ever lived.

296
00:30:26.960 --> 00:30:29.680
Humph.

297
00:30:29.760 --> 00:30:33.360
Say. uh- Could I have
some of that water?

298
00:30:42.680 --> 00:30:47.240
I don't know why I try.

299
00:30:51.840 --> 00:30:54.960
I guess I am gonna die here.
Who cares.

300
00:30:55.040 --> 00:30:56.880
- Here.
- Thanks. friend. Oh!

301
00:30:56.960 --> 00:30:59.240
- What's that?

302
00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:03.120
I'd say
two or three hundred horses.

303
00:31:03.200 --> 00:31:07.000
five or six wagons...
and about a thousand fools.

304
00:31:09.600 --> 00:31:13.240
- Thank you. Ohh-
- Come on. Meegosh.

305
00:31:17.400 --> 00:31:20.960
It's gonna be
all right. little bobbin.

306
00:31:26.680 --> 00:31:30.440
- Everything's gonna be all right.

307
00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:36.600
- Excuse me. sir.
- Out of the way. peck!

308
00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:40.760
Uh. pardon me.

309
00:31:40.800 --> 00:31:42.840
Uh-

310
00:31:48.240 --> 00:31:53.280
Excuse me. sir. We found one
of your babies in our village.

311
00:31:53.320 --> 00:31:56.120
Will you please
take care of her?

312
00:31:56.200 --> 00:32:00.440
We're going into battle. little ones.
Find a woman to take care of her.

313
00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:04.840
They thought you were
a woman. Airk.

314
00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:07.200
Well-

315
00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:11.640
-Madmartigan. what did you do this time?
-Nothing you wouldn't have done.

316
00:32:11.720 --> 00:32:14.000
I always knew
you'd end up in a crow's cage.

317
00:32:14.080 --> 00:32:15.840
At least I'm not
down there herding sheep.

318
00:32:15.920 --> 00:32:17.360
What are you doing this far north?

319
00:32:17.440 --> 00:32:19.360
The Nockmaar army
destroyed Galladoorn.

320
00:32:20.320 --> 00:32:21.600
The castle?

321
00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:24.000
Bavmorda's troops are
crushing everything in sight.

322
00:32:24.080 --> 00:32:25.920
Come on.
Let me out of here. Airk.

323
00:32:26.000 --> 00:32:28.160
Give me a sword.
I'll win this war for you.

324
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:32.400
Madmartigan-
I still serve Galladoorn.

325
00:32:32.480 --> 00:32:34.360
You serve no one.

326
00:32:34.480 --> 00:32:36.600
Remember?

327
00:32:36.680 --> 00:32:39.760
Sit in your coffin and rot.

328
00:32:39.840 --> 00:32:42.760
- Hyah!
- Wait. Airk. You need me!

329
00:32:42.840 --> 00:32:45.160
I'll be around
long after you're dead!

330
00:32:45.240 --> 00:32:47.760
When I get out of here.
I'm gonna cut your head off...

331
00:32:47.840 --> 00:32:49.840
and stick it
on a pig pole!

332
00:33:06.640 --> 00:33:11.200
- I miss Kiaya and the bobbins.

333
00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:18.680
We're running out of food.

334
00:33:18.720 --> 00:33:22.200
Nobody's gonna
take care of that baby.

335
00:33:22.280 --> 00:33:25.120
You know why?
Nobody cares.

336
00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:31.280
Except me.

337
00:33:31.360 --> 00:33:35.400
You want to go back to your families.
I want out of this cage.

338
00:33:35.520 --> 00:33:39.320
Let me take care of that baby.
I'll look after her like she was my own.

339
00:33:39.360 --> 00:33:42.200
I believe he would. Willow.

340
00:33:42.280 --> 00:33:44.760
He doesn't know
anything about babies.

341
00:33:44.800 --> 00:33:49.800
Right. But I know
a lot of women who do.

342
00:33:49.880 --> 00:33:52.680
If I had somebody in my life.

343
00:33:52.760 --> 00:33:56.200
a little daughter. perhaps.

344
00:33:56.280 --> 00:33:59.400
I might have a reason
to go on living.

345
00:34:02.560 --> 00:34:05.200
You can't leave me
in here to die.

346
00:34:05.320 --> 00:34:08.240
Not when all I want
to do is protect her.

347
00:34:20.960 --> 00:34:24.720
I feel better!

348
00:34:24.800 --> 00:34:28.360
-You've done the right thing! -Okay. All right. All right.

349
00:34:28.440 --> 00:34:32.720
- You gotta promise to feed her.
- Come to Daddy. little darlin'.

350
00:34:32.800 --> 00:34:37.600
- And keep her clean.
- Absolutely.

351
00:34:37.680 --> 00:34:39.640
- Hee. hee. hee!

352
00:34:39.720 --> 00:34:44.400
- Wheee!

353
00:34:44.480 --> 00:34:47.600
She likes me.

354
00:34:49.600 --> 00:34:51.880
Here are her changing rags.

355
00:34:51.960 --> 00:34:54.120
- And her milk bladder.
- Any milk in there?

356
00:34:54.160 --> 00:34:58.240
- It's for her!
- I wouldn't steal from a baby.

357
00:34:59.920 --> 00:35:03.280
- You wory too much. peck.

358
00:35:03.400 --> 00:35:07.160
- It's Willow.
- I mean Willow.

359
00:35:07.240 --> 00:35:12.720
Now listen. boys- Willow.
You've done the right thing.

360
00:35:12.840 --> 00:35:16.040
And I want you to get home
and bring your crop in.

361
00:35:22.320 --> 00:35:26.360
- Good-bye. little one.

362
00:35:34.720 --> 00:35:36.880
Please. take good care of her.

363
00:35:38.600 --> 00:35:41.320
I give you my word of honor!

364
00:35:47.720 --> 00:35:51.480
- Meegosh. slow down!
- Oh. come on!

365
00:35:51.520 --> 00:35:55.600
If we hurry. we can be home by
tomorrow morning. We'll be heroes.

366
00:35:55.680 --> 00:35:59.040
- Do you really think so?
- Sure.

367
00:35:59.120 --> 00:36:01.280
"Look. there's
Willow and Meegosh.

368
00:36:01.400 --> 00:36:03.520
The heroes have come home."

369
00:36:03.600 --> 00:36:06.520
"Welcome back. boys.
You deserve medals!"

370
00:36:06.600 --> 00:36:10.680
- Yeah. Medals.

371
00:36:10.720 --> 00:36:14.320
Meegosh-

372
00:36:16.120 --> 00:36:20.080
- Did we do the right thing?
- Absolutely.

373
00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:24.280
- There's nothing to wory about.

374
00:36:27.160 --> 00:36:29.360
Hyah! Ha!

375
00:36:29.440 --> 00:36:34.480
I stole the baby! I stole the baby!

376
00:36:34.560 --> 00:36:38.160
- Hyah!
- That's my baby!

377
00:36:38.240 --> 00:36:40.120
- Stop! Wait! Come back!

378
00:36:40.160 --> 00:36:43.200
Left. you stupid bird.
Left! Ha ha!

379
00:36:45.880 --> 00:36:49.000
- Ah!
- Ow!

380
00:36:49.080 --> 00:36:52.600
Brownies!
Let's get out of here!

381
00:36:52.680 --> 00:36:55.920
- Come on. Meegosh!
- Ow!

382
00:36:56.880 --> 00:37:00.440
- Uhh-uh-huh-uh.
- Uhh. Oww!

383
00:37:01.720 --> 00:37:03.640
We'll outrun 'em!

384
00:37:08.240 --> 00:37:12.120
-Hey. ugly. wake up!-

385
00:37:12.200 --> 00:37:14.560
Huh?

386
00:37:14.640 --> 00:37:19.520
- Stand your ground. He's our prisoner.

387
00:37:19.560 --> 00:37:22.280
Meegosh.
where's the baby?

388
00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:24.200
Bring the Nelwyns tome.

389
00:37:24.200 --> 00:37:25.560
All right. you heard her!

390
00:37:25.640 --> 00:37:29.280
- What's going on?
- Shut up. or I'll break your nose.

391
00:37:29.320 --> 00:37:31.640
You are mine to toy with.

392
00:37:31.680 --> 00:37:35.040
Forward!

393
00:37:35.120 --> 00:37:38.760
- Gimme the rope.

394
00:37:38.840 --> 00:37:42.680
Where-
Where...

395
00:37:42.800 --> 00:37:44.960
did you get that baby?

396
00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:49.560
I stole it from a stupid Daikini.

397
00:37:49.720 --> 00:37:52.760
Franjean. release the Nelwyns.

398
00:37:52.800 --> 00:37:56.960
-And stop pestering them.
- Uh-oh.

399
00:37:57.000 --> 00:37:59.000
Ahh-

400
00:38:01.160 --> 00:38:03.040
- Yaah!

401
00:38:07.160 --> 00:38:10.240
- You!

402
00:38:10.280 --> 00:38:15.160
Welcome to my kingdom.

403
00:38:21.080 --> 00:38:25.400
- I'm happy to meet you. Willow Ufgood.
- How do you know my name?

404
00:38:25.480 --> 00:38:28.640
Blora Danan told me.

405
00:38:28.680 --> 00:38:31.840
Blora?
Blora. Willow is here.

406
00:38:34.520 --> 00:38:39.840
- But she's just a baby.
- She's very special.

407
00:38:39.960 --> 00:38:45.040
My Brownies have been searching for her
ever since we heard she was born.

408
00:38:45.120 --> 00:38:49.840
Blora Danan has chosen you
to be her guardian.

409
00:38:49.920 --> 00:38:54.480
- Me?
- Yes. She likes you.

410
00:38:55.880 --> 00:39:00.640
And Elora Danan knows you
have the courage to help us.

411
00:39:00.720 --> 00:39:04.160
Take my wand
to the sorceress. Find Raziel.

412
00:39:04.200 --> 00:39:08.280
She will guide you and Blora Danan
to the kingdom of Tir Asleen.

413
00:39:08.320 --> 00:39:11.320
where a good king and queen
will look after her.

414
00:39:11.360 --> 00:39:15.000
You need a warrior for
a job like this. I'm a nobody.

415
00:39:15.160 --> 00:39:18.320
Blora. you don't want me.

416
00:39:18.400 --> 00:39:21.920
Tell her.
I'm short. even for a Nelwyn.

417
00:39:24.800 --> 00:39:27.280
Hello?

418
00:39:34.360 --> 00:39:37.600
Blora Danan must survive!

419
00:39:37.640 --> 00:39:42.320
She must fulfill her destiny and bring
about the downfall of Queen Bavmorda.

420
00:39:42.360 --> 00:39:45.120
whose powers are growing
like an evil plague.

421
00:39:45.160 --> 00:39:49.400
Unless she is stopped.
Bavmorda will control the lives...

422
00:39:49.440 --> 00:39:53.840
of your village.
your children- everyone.

423
00:39:58.280 --> 00:40:01.640
All creatures of good heart
need your help. Willow.

424
00:40:01.720 --> 00:40:06.720
The choice is yours.

425
00:40:28.400 --> 00:40:32.480
- Hey. Meegosh. Wake up.
- Huh?

426
00:40:32.520 --> 00:40:36.560
- It's time to go home.
- Home?

427
00:40:39.080 --> 00:40:42.440
Listen. Meegosh.
Tell Kiaya I love her.

428
00:40:42.520 --> 00:40:46.880
- And I think of her every day.
- Willow-

429
00:40:46.960 --> 00:40:50.320
And tell her I'm not going to let
anything happen to the baby.

430
00:40:50.360 --> 00:40:52.920
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

431
00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:55.800
I hope so.

432
00:40:55.880 --> 00:40:59.280
Listen. be careful.

433
00:41:05.160 --> 00:41:09.480
- I know the way. Franjean.
- You always think you know the way.

434
00:41:09.600 --> 00:41:12.880
-I am the leader!
- How long will it take to find Raziel?

435
00:41:12.960 --> 00:41:17.280
Um. not long. She's been exiled
to an island just over those hills.

436
00:41:17.360 --> 00:41:20.320
- She's what?
- Exiled...

437
00:41:20.360 --> 00:41:24.080
by the evil Queen Bavmorda.

438
00:41:24.120 --> 00:41:26.680
Rool. You fool. He does
not need to know everything.

439
00:41:26.760 --> 00:41:29.240
- I didn't tell him everything.
- You told him enough.

440
00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:31.520
- You mentioned the island. the queen.
- Wait a minute.

441
00:41:31.560 --> 00:41:34.120
So?

442
00:41:34.200 --> 00:41:36.840
What do you mean? What are
you saying. mysterious island?

443
00:41:36.960 --> 00:41:39.440
Don't play with that wand.

444
00:41:39.520 --> 00:41:41.960
Cherlindrea told you
it holds vast powers.

445
00:41:42.040 --> 00:41:44.440
Only a great sorcerer can use it.

446
00:41:44.520 --> 00:41:47.120
-Not a stupid peck like you.

447
00:41:47.200 --> 00:41:50.240
- This way.
- No. No. No. I don't think so.

448
00:41:50.320 --> 00:41:52.480
- All right. then this way.
- Bah. nope.

449
00:41:52.560 --> 00:41:55.000
- This way.
- This way?

450
00:41:55.040 --> 00:41:58.680
- That's what I said.
- This way.

451
00:41:58.720 --> 00:42:02.000
- You know where you're going?
- Of course.

452
00:42:02.080 --> 00:42:04.680
With us as your guides
no harm with befall you.

453
00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:18.680
- Take it up!

454
00:42:20.160 --> 00:42:24.200
- We are not going in there!
- But Blora needs fresh milk.

455
00:42:24.280 --> 00:42:28.920
- And we are drenched.
- You are not in command. shorty. I am!

456
00:42:29.000 --> 00:42:32.480
- You hear me?
- Whoa!

457
00:43:08.680 --> 00:43:11.000
- Excuse me? Excuse me.

458
00:43:11.040 --> 00:43:13.880
Could you spare some milk
for this poor. hungry baby?

459
00:43:13.960 --> 00:43:15.760
Get out of here. peck!

460
00:43:15.840 --> 00:43:18.120
Get outta here
or we'll cook ya!

461
00:43:30.920 --> 00:43:34.680
Ooh. look at her!

462
00:43:34.720 --> 00:43:36.960
I could use
a love potion on her!

463
00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:40.680
Franjean! Hey! Give me that
dust of broken heart.

464
00:43:40.760 --> 00:43:42.360
- Come on! Give it to me!
- Let go of me!

465
00:43:42.480 --> 00:43:45.680
It's very dangerous.
It belongs to the fairies!

466
00:43:49.680 --> 00:43:51.600
Hey. quiet!
You want to get us killed?

467
00:43:58.280 --> 00:44:01.920
Oh. Rool! Always playing
with those fairy love potions.

468
00:44:04.120 --> 00:44:09.040
You are so beautiful!

469
00:44:09.080 --> 00:44:12.600
- Your eyes! Your whiskers!

470
00:44:12.680 --> 00:44:15.200
- I have to kiss you!
-Rool!

471
00:44:15.280 --> 00:44:16.920
That dust of broken heart!

472
00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:33.320
Beer!

473
00:44:36.280 --> 00:44:38.320
These people are crazy!
This could be bad!

474
00:44:42.720 --> 00:44:44.640
Hurry! Hurry!

475
00:44:44.720 --> 00:44:46.520
My husband's coming!

476
00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:48.560
If he catches you here.
he'll kill us both!

477
00:44:48.640 --> 00:44:51.200
- How do I look?
- Not you!

478
00:44:52.320 --> 00:44:54.160
Where the hell
did you come from?

479
00:44:54.240 --> 00:44:56.440
I knew I shouldn't
have trusted you.

480
00:44:56.480 --> 00:45:00.160
Don't I know you?
I stole the baby from you. Daikini.

481
00:45:00.240 --> 00:45:02.360
- While you were taking a pee-pee!
- Cover your face!

482
00:45:02.400 --> 00:45:05.920
- You are crawling with Brownies.
- I hate Brownies!

483
00:45:05.960 --> 00:45:08.680
Whoa!

484
00:45:08.760 --> 00:45:11.200
- Where is he? Where?
- Hello. dear.

485
00:45:11.280 --> 00:45:13.600
There's nobody here but
me and. uh. my. uh-

486
00:45:13.640 --> 00:45:15.920
- I'll kill him!
- ...my cousin. Hilda.

487
00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:18.200
- Hilda?
- Hilda.

488
00:45:18.240 --> 00:45:20.240
- Oh. Hilda!
- This is my husband. Llug.

489
00:45:20.320 --> 00:45:23.000
- Mmm... Big husband.
- Yes.

490
00:45:23.040 --> 00:45:24.840
- How do you do?

491
00:45:24.880 --> 00:45:27.160
Hilda! Ooh.

492
00:45:27.240 --> 00:45:29.280
Come on. girly.
Don't be shy.

493
00:45:29.360 --> 00:45:31.840
- Hey! Give her back!

494
00:45:31.920 --> 00:45:34.240
- Pecks make terrible nursemaids.
- Nursemaid?

495
00:45:34.280 --> 00:45:37.120
- They get too excited.

496
00:45:37.120 --> 00:45:39.680
Excuse me!
Are we having a party?

497
00:45:39.760 --> 00:45:41.720
- Huh?
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!

498
00:45:41.760 --> 00:45:46.240
- Stop. please. Ooh.

499
00:45:46.320 --> 00:45:48.120
Come on.
Fight like a man!

500
00:45:48.160 --> 00:45:51.080
- Want to breed?

501
00:45:51.120 --> 00:45:54.000
Tempting. but no.

502
00:45:56.800 --> 00:45:58.680
Thank you.
Time to leave.

503
00:45:58.720 --> 00:46:00.600
- Bye. Hilda!
- Take them out.

504
00:46:00.640 --> 00:46:03.680
- Hey! Come along!

505
00:46:03.760 --> 00:46:06.240
- Careful. you lout!
- Move along!

506
00:46:06.320 --> 00:46:08.960
Gather pall these babies.

507
00:46:09.000 --> 00:46:11.200
That baby over there.
Let me see its arm.

508
00:46:14.760 --> 00:46:16.800
That's not the one.

509
00:46:20.360 --> 00:46:23.000
You! Are you the mother
of that child?

510
00:46:23.080 --> 00:46:25.600
- Yes. Yes. I am.
- Let me see it.

511
00:46:25.680 --> 00:46:27.160
No! Don't let her!

512
00:46:27.280 --> 00:46:28.640
Aah!

513
00:46:28.720 --> 00:46:31.480
I gave you an order. woman!

514
00:46:40.480 --> 00:46:43.760
You-
You're... beautiful.

515
00:46:43.880 --> 00:46:47.080
- And you're very strong.
- Thank you.

516
00:46:49.560 --> 00:46:51.960
You're no woman!

517
00:46:52.040 --> 00:46:53.800
- Now. honey. take it easy.
- Not a woman?

518
00:46:53.880 --> 00:46:56.640
- Gentlemen.
- Not a woman?

519
00:46:56.680 --> 00:46:59.360
- Meet Llug.

520
00:47:00.560 --> 00:47:02.520
- After them!
- Out of the way!

521
00:47:08.600 --> 00:47:09.800
- To the horses!

522
00:47:09.800 --> 00:47:10.800
- To the horses!

523
00:47:13.280 --> 00:47:15.600
Hey! What are you doing?

524
00:47:19.840 --> 00:47:21.680
- Hyah!

525
00:47:21.760 --> 00:47:25.520
Madmartigan!
Madmartigan! Wait!

526
00:47:28.800 --> 00:47:33.480
- He's not a woman!
- To your horses! Hyah! Hyah!

527
00:47:33.560 --> 00:47:35.880
Don't let them get away!

528
00:47:37.440 --> 00:47:40.760
- Madmartigan. stop!
- What?

529
00:47:52.040 --> 00:47:54.000
Hyah!

530
00:47:58.920 --> 00:48:01.360
Madmartigan.
I'm warning you-

531
00:48:03.280 --> 00:48:06.840
- Ow!
- Prepare to die!

532
00:48:29.280 --> 00:48:31.480
Madmartigan!
Stop!

533
00:49:00.360 --> 00:49:02.320
Franjean. help me!

534
00:49:06.760 --> 00:49:08.600
- Rool!
- Help!

535
00:49:08.680 --> 00:49:11.600
Rool! Rool.

536
00:49:12.680 --> 00:49:16.360
- Rool! What are you doing?
- Help me!

537
00:49:21.520 --> 00:49:23.680
- Come on. I am.
- Pull me in.

538
00:49:23.760 --> 00:49:26.080
Yeah. pull!

539
00:49:43.520 --> 00:49:45.440
You can't have her!

540
00:49:51.120 --> 00:49:52.800
Whoa!

541
00:49:57.320 --> 00:50:00.720
- Rool. this isn't funny!

542
00:50:00.840 --> 00:50:02.680
Help me cut the rope!

543
00:50:15.320 --> 00:50:17.960
Who-oa!

544
00:50:38.600 --> 00:50:41.080
Willow. stay down!

545
00:50:44.640 --> 00:50:46.560
Whoa!

546
00:50:46.640 --> 00:50:48.800
Whoa!

547
00:50:48.880 --> 00:50:50.720
Gone crazy?

548
00:50:50.800 --> 00:50:52.840
You can't chase around
with Elora like this.

549
00:50:52.880 --> 00:50:55.240
- We're getting off!
- Hyah!

550
00:50:55.280 --> 00:50:57.760
Oh! Hold on! Hyah!

551
00:51:19.680 --> 00:51:22.080
Whoa! Whoa!

552
00:51:25.120 --> 00:51:27.360
- Oh. Rool.

553
00:51:27.440 --> 00:51:30.960
Now we stop. peck.

554
00:51:31.040 --> 00:51:36.080
Stupid Daikini.
Ask him to stop the wagon.

555
00:51:36.120 --> 00:51:40.200
Madmartigan! You never. ever
drive that fast with an infant!

556
00:51:41.600 --> 00:51:44.040
I just saved that infant's life!

557
00:51:45.400 --> 00:51:47.680
Hah! Hah!

558
00:51:47.760 --> 00:51:49.640
Gather your wits. Come on.

559
00:51:49.680 --> 00:51:52.600
- Don't wory about me.
-Come on!

560
00:51:53.640 --> 00:51:55.680
- Get down!

561
00:51:55.760 --> 00:51:58.080
Uh. where am I?
Oh!

562
00:51:59.920 --> 00:52:01.920
Rool. you fool.
get out of the road!

563
00:52:17.760 --> 00:52:20.200
-Ah. Franjean!
- You better clear out. Willow.

564
00:52:20.280 --> 00:52:21.720
Before those troops come back.

565
00:52:21.760 --> 00:52:25.080
- Ah. my head!
- We don't need him. Blora.

566
00:52:33.120 --> 00:52:35.120
Madmartigan. wait!

567
00:52:35.160 --> 00:52:38.400
Go home. Willow!
It's a dangerous world.

568
00:52:38.480 --> 00:52:40.360
Yeah. and that's why
we need your help.

569
00:52:40.440 --> 00:52:43.480
My help? What do you need my help for?

570
00:52:43.560 --> 00:52:45.680
You're a sorcerer!

571
00:52:45.760 --> 00:52:48.840
You're a great warrior.
and a swordsman.

572
00:52:48.920 --> 00:52:51.680
And you're ten times
bigger than I am. stupid!

573
00:52:51.760 --> 00:52:54.840
Are you tying to make my life
more difficult than it already is?

574
00:52:58.000 --> 00:53:02.720
- Hurry! Big dogs!

575
00:53:02.800 --> 00:53:06.880
Look. I'm sorry
I got angry.

576
00:53:06.880 --> 00:53:08.760
We wouldn't have
escaped without you.

577
00:53:22.400 --> 00:53:25.120
Well. don't expect me
to help you again.

578
00:53:26.560 --> 00:53:30.040
Good! Then we go that way!
To the lake!

579
00:53:31.040 --> 00:53:34.040
That way.

580
00:53:34.080 --> 00:53:37.600
You are drunk. and when you
are drunk you forget that...

581
00:53:37.680 --> 00:53:39.520
- I am in charge!
- You are in charge.

582
00:53:39.600 --> 00:53:41.680
Fine.
Then which way do we go?

583
00:53:41.760 --> 00:53:43.720
That way!

584
00:53:46.640 --> 00:53:50.960
Oh. no!
That's the way I'm going.

585
00:53:51.000 --> 00:53:53.880
All right. all right. You can
follow me as far as the lake.

586
00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:56.120
But that's it!

587
00:53:56.160 --> 00:53:59.800
- You're not going south. are you?
- No. just as far as the lake.

588
00:53:59.840 --> 00:54:04.800
Good. Mumbo-Jumbo. I am hungry.
Go and get me some eggs or something.

589
00:54:04.880 --> 00:54:07.400
- We are not afraid of you!
- Now!

590
00:54:13.840 --> 00:54:18.280
Kael. have you found the child?

591
00:54:18.400 --> 00:54:20.040
The search goes on. my queen.

592
00:54:21.080 --> 00:54:23.040
Why. with my powers.

593
00:54:23.120 --> 00:54:26.200
with the strength
of my great army.

594
00:54:26.280 --> 00:54:29.520
can you not find
one little child?

595
00:54:29.600 --> 00:54:31.840
We look even now.
It won't be long.

596
00:54:31.920 --> 00:54:35.120
Find the child.
Find the child!

597
00:54:35.200 --> 00:54:37.720
Time is running out.

598
00:54:41.680 --> 00:54:45.960
- Good night.

599
00:54:46.000 --> 00:54:49.160
She is kinda cute.

600
00:54:49.280 --> 00:54:50.920
When she's quiet.

601
00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:54.160
She's really a princess.

602
00:54:54.240 --> 00:54:58.080
Really?
And you're a great sorcerer.

603
00:54:58.160 --> 00:55:00.000
And I'm the king of Cashmere.

604
00:55:00.080 --> 00:55:03.720
Go to sleep. Willow.

605
00:55:03.800 --> 00:55:06.200
Good night. Madmartigan.

606
00:55:06.240 --> 00:55:09.120
Rats! Big rats! Rats!

607
00:55:09.160 --> 00:55:12.360
Uh- Uh! Oh!
Rats! Ra-

608
00:55:12.400 --> 00:55:15.240
Oh. Rool. you had
that stupid rat dream!

609
00:55:25.600 --> 00:55:28.200
Tuatha...

610
00:55:28.280 --> 00:55:30.360
Lawkathok...

611
00:55:30.440 --> 00:55:32.280
- Tuatha!

612
00:55:32.280 --> 00:55:34.920
Huh?
Willow?

613
00:55:35.960 --> 00:55:38.040
Willow?

614
00:55:39.680 --> 00:55:42.080
Oh. There you are.

615
00:55:42.160 --> 00:55:44.040
Madmartigan!

616
00:55:44.120 --> 00:55:47.320
'Night. Willow.

617
00:55:58.920 --> 00:56:00.840
This way! This way!

618
00:56:12.160 --> 00:56:14.040
What are you doing?

619
00:56:14.080 --> 00:56:16.360
I found some black root.
She loves it!

620
00:56:16.440 --> 00:56:19.240
Black root? I am
the father of two children.

621
00:56:19.320 --> 00:56:21.240
and you never. ever
give a baby black root.

622
00:56:21.400 --> 00:56:24.320
Well. my mother
raised us on black root.

623
00:56:24.400 --> 00:56:26.840
It's good for ya!
It puts hair on your chest.

624
00:56:26.920 --> 00:56:29.560
- Doesn't it. Sticks?
- Her name is not Sticks.

625
00:56:29.520 --> 00:56:32.360
She's Blora Danan.
the future empress of Tir Asleen.

626
00:56:32.400 --> 00:56:34.640
And the last thing she's gonna
want is a hairy chest!

627
00:56:38.680 --> 00:56:40.640
Did you see what he did?

628
00:56:40.720 --> 00:56:43.840
He stole our black root. I'll get
some more. don't wory about it.

629
00:56:48.520 --> 00:56:51.760
- There it is! The island!

630
00:56:53.840 --> 00:56:55.720
We made it.

631
00:56:55.800 --> 00:57:00.120
We have led you to
the island of the sorceress Fin Raziel.

632
00:57:00.240 --> 00:57:04.320
- We'll get a boat in that village.
- A big boat.

633
00:57:21.720 --> 00:57:23.640
Well. looks like
I got you here.

634
00:57:23.760 --> 00:57:26.080
You!
What did you do?

635
00:57:26.160 --> 00:57:29.040
All you did was hang around
and eat our eggs! Huh?

636
00:57:29.120 --> 00:57:31.040
I found a boat.
We're all set.

637
00:57:31.080 --> 00:57:34.880
Good. Take these two lizards
out and drown them.

638
00:57:35.000 --> 00:57:38.200
- Who are you calling lizards?
- Heh? Heh?

639
00:57:40.200 --> 00:57:42.760
Your mother was lizard!

640
00:57:45.640 --> 00:57:48.040
- Good-bye. Sticks.

641
00:57:50.640 --> 00:57:53.440
If you really are a princess.

642
00:57:53.520 --> 00:57:56.360
take care of him.

643
00:58:02.480 --> 00:58:05.640
- Madmartigan!
- What?

644
00:58:05.720 --> 00:58:07.520
Thanks.

645
00:58:16.680 --> 00:58:19.120
Hey! Aah!

646
00:58:19.200 --> 00:58:22.440
-Keep walkin'. hero!
- Don't even turnaround!

